The paper discusses a novel approach for applying strong local consistencies (SLCs) to constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs) using parallelization. This involves running multiple slave processes, each implementing a SLC method, alongside a master CSP solver. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as CSPs are a subfield of AI, and the paper proposes a new approach for solving CSPs. It could also be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the paper discusses parallelization techniques. Additionally, the paper could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes new algorithms for solving CSPs. It could also be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages) as the paper discusses the implementation of SLC methods. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as the paper proposes a new approach for improving the performance of CSP solvers.
